pageContext.description: Loop is cracked right through. Earth resembling clay adheres nearly all over.
pageContext.patina: Some light greenish bronze and blue patina.
pageContext.surface: A little rough. A good deal of heavy encrustment.
pageContext.associations: Part of a hoard consisting of 9 socketed celts, a spear head, 2 gouges, portion of a knife, etc. and a socketed celt now in the Museum of the Royal Academy of Literature, History, and Antiquities, Stockholm + an equal weight of rough ore (copper cake?)
pageContext.collection: Private Collection,C.H. Grinling, Esq.,17 Rectory Place, Woolrich, SE 18,1920,Obtained from Joseph Fels, Esq., the owner of Basildon Farm.
